<body>
    <h1>
        How to Use a Linux Terminal
    </h1>
    <h3>Open the terminal</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Click the "Teminal" icon (grey box filled with black with an arrow and underscore inside) in the sidebar</li>
	<li>Search the computer for "Terminal"</li>
    </ol>
    <h3>Common Commands</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>cd</li>
	<ul>
	    <li>Change Directory</li>
	    <li>"cd .." to go up a directory</li>
	    <li>"cd dir" to go into directory dir</li>
	    <li>"cd dir/ex" to go into dir's sub-directory ex"
	    <li>"cd ../dir" to go up one directory and then down into directory dir</li>
	    <li>"cd ~/dir" to go to the root directory and then down into directory dir</li>
	    <li>These commands can be arranged and stacked as much as needed to define the complete directory path</li>
	</ul>
        <li>mv</li>
	<ul>
	    <li>Move a file to a new location</li>
	</ul>
        <li>ls</li>
	<ul>
	    <li>List all files within the current directory</li>
	</ul>
    </ul>
